  "texts": [
    "Well-known CNNs, which are intended to be used in this work, are ResNet-50, DenseNet-201, and VGG-16, since such networks have strong capabilities concerning feature extraction and may be appropriate for medical images.",
    "The U-Net, with its encoder-decoder architecture, remains a gold standard for performing precise segmentation.",
    "DWT can bring about an enhanced representation of features in both the spatial and frequency domains required by subtlety in details inherent in medical images, while SVM ensures maximum class separability at the least computational cost.",
    "This hybrid approach provides a good balance between computational efficiency and classification accuracy, achieving 92.3% testing accuracy with an IoU of 0.93, making this approach highly suitable for the medium-sized CKHK-22 dataset.",
    "Despite the presence of modern architectures such as ViTs, which indeed perform well, their generalization requires much larger datasets and higher computational resources, thereby limiting their applicability in clinical resource-constrained settings."
  ],
